  "instructions": [
    "Heat the olive oil in a large clay pot over medium heat.",
    "Add the red onion and cook until softened, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the garlic and ginger and cook for an additional minute.",
    "Add the dates, soy sauce, lacquer glaze, cinnamon, cumin, paprika, salt, and black pepper. Stir to combine.",
    "Add the chicken broth and bring the mixture to a simmer.",
    "Cover the pot and transfer it to the oven. Bake at 300°F for 25 minutes.",
    "Remove the pot from the oven and let it cool slightly.",
    "Serve the tagine over couscous, garnished with fresh herbs if desired.",
    "Reheat the tagine over low heat, if necessary, before serving."
